QQ0VZ1ggQO1aVf_GK6kn5g
I've eaten at Braggs about a dozen times, have always been greeted with an enthusiastic smile and the feeling of hanging with friends. My hands down favorite is their French Toast...so fresh and delicious, every time. I'm not a vegan or vegetarian but love having the options when dining with friends and family who are. The small space is quite cozy-a couple of times I've even joined a table of strangers just because they were so busy with limited seating. Met some cool people that way-they seem to attract interesting, open minded types, probably because they are that way, themselves. Eat whatever strikes your fancy-there really are no bad choices. Every plate is a winner! Go-and be a winner too!

